<p>
<center><b>INTRODUCTION</b><p>
</center><p>
	The following bibliography contains the peer-reviewed publications
("publications"), non-peer-reviewed publications &amp; reports ("reports"), and
abstracts for oral presentations &amp; poster displays ("abstracts") which were
prepared by Northeast Fisheries Science Center (NEFSC) employees, and which
have a 1994 publication date.  Some of the publications, reports, and abstracts
by NEFSC employees deal more with administrative than scientific matters.
Consequently, not all works are appropriate for inclusion in this bibliography.
Only those works are included which have been specifically identified and
provided by the NEFSC's Executive Staff.  Authors who were NEFSC employees at
the time they composed their works, and/or who were Center employees during
1994, are denoted in the list by all capital letters.<p>
<p>
	Editorial treatment of bibliographic entries is largely based on the CBE style
manual, fifth edition<sup>1</sup>.  Three abbreviations used throughout the
bibliography need to be explained:  (1) "n.p." means the work--usually an
abstract--is not paginated; (2) "n.n.k." means the volume number of the work is
not known--a result of not having the actual work in hand in order to prepare
its bibliographic entry; and (3) "p.n.k." means the page number(s) of the work
is(are) not known--again, a result of not having the actual work in hand in
order to prepare its bibliographic entry.  Also, there are many foreign
recipients of this bibliography, most of whom do not use English as a primary
language.  Because English-language-based acronyms are particularly difficult
to comprehend by non-English-using readers, the standardized abbreviations of
these acronyms have been included within squared brackets immediately following
the acronyms.<p>
<p>
<p>
____________________<p>
<p>
<sup>1</sup>Neter, E. (chairman); Altman, P.L.; Burgan, M.W.; Holmgren, N.H.;
Pollock, G.; Zipf, E.M.  1983.  CBE style manual: a guide for authors, editors,
and publishers in the biological sciences. 5th ed.  Bethesda, MD: Council of
Biology Editors; 324 p.<p>
