<title>Fisheries Information Gathering Techniques</title>
<body bgcolor="#F8f8ff">

<p align=center>
<img src="/images/finfo2.gif"><br>
<p align=center>
<blockquote>
<iMG align=right width=350 height=275 SRC="/images/portintv.jpg">

<b>

Wonder what life is like aboard a research vessel? To find out read the <a
href="volman.html">volunteer manual</a> which is given to all volunteers and
first time sailors.
<p>

Descriptions of work to be done aboard three crusies scheduled in 1996. <br>
1.  <a href="veslink1.html">NOAA ALBATROSS IV 96-06, May 20-31 </a><br>
2.  <a href="veslink2.html">NOAA ALBATROSS IV 96-08, June 17-28</a><br>
3.  <a href="veslink3.html">NOAA ALBATROSS IV 96-10, Aug. 28 - Sept. 6.</a><p>


<p>

<img src="/images/noaabullet.gif"></a>The National Marine Fisheries
Service provides the various Regional Fishery Management Councils
with stock assessments that are used to help determine that portion of
the fish stock which may be harvested (optimum yield), given certain
management objectives. Fishermen have commonly asked <i>
<A HREF="/method/method.html">"How did you guys come up with those numbers
anyway?</a></i>"  While this report (which was created by the State of
Massachusetts in the late 70's) is somewhat out of date, it gives a
general idea about data gathering techniques.  <p>

<img src="/images/noaabullet.gif"></a><b><A HREF="/library/sos94/fishobs/fishobs.html">Fishery Observer Program</a></b>
The Northeast Fisheries Science Center has conducted a large scale
program in which trained scientific observers are sent to sea aboard
commercial fishing vessels.   This year observers will sample on about
1,600 fishing trips and collectively spend the equivalent of 10 years
at sea.  <p>

<img src="/images/noaabullet.gif"></a><b><A HREF="/library/sos94/vesurv/vesurv.html">Research Vessel Surveys</b></a> 
Fishery-dependent data are vital to our ability to monitor stocks,
and often are the only reliable source of data concerning some
species.  However, using of fishery-dependent data alone may
severely limit our ability to evaluate some stocks, and to make
predictions.For these and other reasons, fishery scientists
throughout the world have initiated research vessel sampling
programs to gather fishery-independent information.<p>

</blockquote>
<p><a href="/noaa.html" TARGET=_top><img height=50 width=30
src="/images/sfbairdicon.gif"><br>Home</a>

