Mid-

coast
Closure Area, and the Massachusetts Bay Closure Area,
as defined in paragraphs (a)(1), (c)(1), (f)(1), (g)(1), and
(h)(1), respectively, of this section, provided that their gear
is stowed in accordance with the provisions of paragraph (e) of
this section.
<p>    (e) Gear stowage requirements.  Vessels transiting the
closed areas must stow their gear as follows:
*    *    *    *    *
<p>      (f) Northeast Closure Area.  (1) During the period August
15 through September 13, no fishing vessel or person on a fishing
vessel may enter, fish, or be, and no fishing gear capable of
catching multispecies finfish, unless otherwise allowed in this
part may be, in the area known as the Northeast Closure Area
(Figure 3 to part 651), as defined by straight lines connecting
the following points in the order stated, except as specified in
paragraphs (d) and (f)(2) of this section:
<p>
