<area SHAPE="RECT"  COORDS="8,652,229,678" HREF="http://www.wh.whoi.edu/">
</map>

<A HREF = "/cgi-bin/imagemap/amend7"><img border=0 alt="Navagation Bar, turn on
images." src="c1.jpg"
USEMAP="#navbar" ISMAP></a>

</td>

<td valign=top>
<img border=0 width=453 height=80 alt="Regulated Mesh Area Regulations" src="d1a.gif">

<i>All vessels fishing, harvesting, possessing, or landing multispecies
finfish in or from the EEZ and all vessels holding a Federal
multispecies permit must comply with the following minimum mesh size
restrictions, unless otherwise exempted.</i><p>

<a name="gom1"><a href="#gom">Gulf of Maine/Georges Bank (GOM/GB) Regulated Mesh
Area<p></a></a>

The minimum mesh size, unless further restricted by the Stellwagen
Bank/Jeffreys Ledge juvenile protection area or unless fishing under
the <a href="#das">Large Mesh Days- at- Sea (DAS) program</a>, is 6 inch square or diamond
throughout the entire net.  For exemptions to this mesh requirement in
this area, refer to <a href="sme.html">Fact Sheet 4</a>, Small Mesh Exemptions.  <p>

<a name="swj1"><a href="#swj">Stellwagen Bank/Jeffreys Ledge (SB/JL) Juvenile
Protection Area</a><p> 
</a>

Vessels other than gillnet vessels, fishing in the SB/JL area are
required to have a minimum of 6 inch square mesh in the last 50 bars of
the codend and extension piece for vessels 45 ft  in length and less,
and in the last 100 bars of the codend and extension piece for vessels
greater than 45 ft in length.  Gillnet vessels must use a minimum of 6
inch diamond mesh.<p>

<a name="sne1"><a href="#sne">Southern New England (SNE) Regulated Mesh
Area</a></a><p>

The minimum mesh size, unless fishing under the <a href="#das">Large Mesh
DAS program</a>, is 6 inch square or diamond mesh throughout the entire
net.  For exemptions to this mesh requirement in this area, refer to
<a href="sme.html">Fact Sheet 4.</a> <p> 

<a name="mam1"><a href="#mam">Mid- Atlantic (MA) Regulated Mesh Area</a></a><p>

The minimum mesh size, unless fishing under the Large Mesh DAS program,
is 51/2 inch diamond mesh or 6 inch square mesh applied throughout the
codend for at least 75 continuous meshes forward of the terminus of the net,
or, for codends with less than 75 meshes,

</td></tr> 
</table>
<!---End  main Table -->


<!--- Main Table sets total width-->
<table width=700 border=0>
<td>
the minimum mesh size codend must be a minimum of one- third of
the net, measured from the terminus of the codend to the head rope,
excluding any turtle excluder devise extension.  For exemptions to this
mesh requirement in this area, refer to <a href="sme.html">Fact Sheet
4.</a><p>

<img width=700 height=40 alt="Regulated Mesh Area Map & Coords." src="d1b.gif"><p>
<center>
<img width=529 height=442 alt="Map" border=0 src="map1.gif"><p>
</center>
<a name="gom"><a href="#gom1">The Gulf of Maine/Georges Bank Regulated Mesh
Area</a></a><p>

<pre>
