<td valign=top>
<img border=0 width=453 height=40 alt="Small Mesh Exemptions" src="g1a.gif"><p>
<img border=0 width=453 height=376 alt="SME Map" src="map4a.gif"><p>

<b>Gulf of Maine/Georges Bank (GOM/GB) Regulated Mesh
Area</b><p>
<p>
Vessels may fish with, use, or possess nets of mesh smaller than the minimum
size specified in the GOM/GB regulated mesh area when fishing in the:<p>

</td></tr> 
</table>
<!---End  main Table -->

<!--- Main Table sets total width-->
<table width=700 border=0>
<td>

<p>
<b>Northern Shrimp Fishery </b><p>

within the Small- Mesh Exemption Area as defined by the following coordinates, provided
the vessel complies with the specifications listed below.<p>

<b>Small- Mesh Exemption Area</b><p>

<pre>
<b>Latitude	Longitude </b>   <a href="map4.html">Map</a>

41 35' N.	70 00' W.
41 35' N.	69 40' W.
42 49.5' N.	69 40' W.
43 12' N.	69 00' W.
43 41' N.	68 00' W.
43 58' N.	67 22' W.
		(the U.S.- Canada Maritime Boundary)
(1)              (1)
</pre>

(1) Northward along the irregular U.S.- Canada
maritime boundary to the shoreline.

<p>
<b>Northern Shrimp Fishery Specifications<p></b>

a)	Vessels must have a properly configured and installed finfish excluder
device in any net with mesh smaller than the minimum specified size. The
finfish excluder device must be configured and installed consistent with the
proper specifications.<p>

b)	Vessels may only fish under this exemption during the northern shrimp
season, as established by the Atlantic States Marine Fisheries Commission
(ASMFC). The northern shrimp season is December 1 through May 30, or as
modified by the ASMFC.<p>

c)	In addition to shrimp, the following species may be retained, with the
restrictions noted, as allowable bycatch species in the northern shrimp
fishery: Longhorn sculpin; up to two standard boxes or totes of silver hake
(whiting); monkfish and monkfish parts up to 10 percent by weight of all other
species on board; and American lobster up to 10 percent by weight of all other
species on board or two hundred lobsters, whichever is less. <p>


<b>Cultivator Shoal Whiting (Silver Hake) Fishery Exemption Area </b><p>

as defined by the following coordinates, provided the vessel complies with
the specifications listed below.<p>

<b>Cultivator Shoal Whiting Fishery Exemption Area</b><p>
<pre>
<b>Latitude     Longitude </b>   <a href="map4.html">Map</a>

42 10' N.	68 10' W.
41 30' N.	68 41' W.
41 30' N.	68 30' W.
41 12.8' N.	68 30' W.
41 05' N.	68 20' W.
41 55' N.	67 40' W.
42 10' N.	68 10' W.
</pre>

<b>Cultivator Shoal Whiting Specifications<p></b>

a)	Vessels fishing in this fishery must have on board an authorizing letter
issued by the Regional Director.<p>

b)	Vessels must comply with a minimum mesh size of 3 inches applied to the
first 160 meshes counted from the terminus of the net.<p>

c)	Authorized vessels may fish under this exemption during the season of June
15 through October 31, unless otherwise specified by publication of a
notification in the Federal Register. <p>

d)	When transiting through the GOM/GB regulated mesh area, nets of mesh smaller
than the regulated mesh size must be stowed properly.<p>

e)	In addition to whiting, the following species may be retained, with the
restrictions noted, as allowable bycatch species in the Cultivator Shoal
whiting fishery exemption area: longhorn sculpin, squid, butterfish, and
mackerel; red hake, dogfish, monkfish and monkfish parts
up to 10 percent by weight of all other species on board; and American lobster
up to 10 percent by weight of all other species on board or two hundred
lobsters, whichever is less. 
<p>

<b>Small Mesh Area 1/Small Mesh Area 2 Exemption Areas</b><p>
 as defined by the following coordinates,provided the vessel complies with
the specifications listed below.<p>

<b>Small Mesh Area 1</b><p>
<pre>
<b>Latitude		Latitude </b>   <a href="map4.html">Map</a>

43 03' N.		70 27' W.
42 57' N.		70 22' W.
42 47' N.		70 32' W.
42 45' N.		70 29' W.
42 43' N.		70 32' W.
42 44' N.		70 39' W.
42 49' N.		70 43' W.
42 50' N.		70 41' W.
42 53' N.		70 43' W.
42 55' N.		70 40' W.
42 59' N.		70 32' W.
43 03' N.		70 27' W.
  
<b>Small Mesh Area 2</b>

<b>Latitude		Longitude </b>   <a href="map4.html">Map</a>

43 20.3' N.		69 59.4' W.
43 25.9' N.		69 45.6' W.
42 49.5' N.		69 40' W.
42 41.5' N.		69 40' W.
42 34.9' N.		70 00' W.
43 20.3' N.		69 59.4' W.

</pre>
<b>Small Mesh Area 1*/Small Mesh Area 2 Specifications<p></b>

a)	For Small Mesh Area I, the fishing season is July 15 through
November 15.  For Small Mesh Area 2, the season is January 1 through June
30.
<p>

b)	Vessels may fish for, possess on board, or land the following species of
fish: Butterfish, dogfish, herring, mackerel, ocean pout, scup, squid, silver
hake (whiting), and red hake.  In addition, the following species of fish may be
retained, with the restrictions noted, as bycatch: Longhorn sculpin; monkfish
and monkfish parts up to 10 percent by weight of all other species on board;
and American lobster up to 10 percent by weight of all other species on board
or two hundred lobsters, whichever is less.<p>

*Vessel operators are reminded that portions of Small Mesh Area I fall within
the state jurisdiction of Massachusetts and New Hampshire.  When fishing in
state waters, vessel operators are subject to the more restrictive of federal
or state regulations.<p>

<b>Nantucket Shoals Dogfish Fishery Exemption Area  <p></b>

as defined by the following coordinates, provided the vessel complies with the
specifications listed below.<p>

<b>Nantucket Shoals Dogfish Exemption Area</b><p>
<pre>
<b>Latitude		Longitude </b><p>   <a href="map4.html">Map</a>

41 45' N.		70 00' W.
41 45' N.		69 20' W.
41 30' N.		69 20' W.
41 30' N.		69 23' W.
41 26.5' N.		69 20' W.
40 50' W.		69 20' N.
40 50' W.		70 00' N.
41 45' N.		70 00' W.
</pre><p>

<b>Nantucket Shoals Dogfish Fishery Exemption Area Specifications</b><p>

a)	Vessels fishing in this fishery must have on board an authorizing letter
issued by the Regional Director.<p>

b)	Authorized vessels may fish under this exemption during the season of June 1
through October 15.<p>

c)	When transiting the GOM/GB regulated mesh area, nets of mesh smaller than
the regulated mesh size must be stowed properly.<p>

d)	In addition to dogfish, the following species may be retained, with the
restrictions noted, as allowable bycatch species in the Nantucket Shoals
dogfish fishery exemption area: Longhorn sculpin, up to two standard totes of
silver hake (whiting); monkfish and monkfish parts up to 10 percent by weight
of all other species on board; American lobster up to 10 percent by weight of
all other species on board or two hundred lobsters, whichever is less; and
skate or skate parts up to 10 percent by weight of all other species on
board.<p>

e)	Authorized vessels must comply with any additional gear restrictions
specified in the authorization letter issued by the Regional Director.<p>

<b>Southern New England (SNE) Regulated Mesh Area</b><p>
See Area definition in <a href="rmar.html">Fact Sheet 1</a><p>

Vessels may fish for, harvest, possess, or land the following exempted species
when fishing with nets of mesh smaller than the minimum size specified in the
SNE regulated mesh area: Butterfish, dogfish (trawl vessels only), herring,
mackerel, ocean pout, scup, shrimp, squid, summer flounder, silver hake
(whiting), and weakfish.  In addition, the following species may be retained,
with the restrictions noted, as incidental take to these exempted fisheries:
Conger eels; searobins; black sea bass; red hake; tautog (blackfish); blowfish
(puffer); cunner; John Dory; mullet; bluefish; tilefish; longhorn sculpin;
fourspot flounder; alewife; hickory shad; American shad; blueback herring; sea
ravens; Atlantic croaker; spot;swordfish; monkfish and monkfish parts up to 10
percent by weight of all other species on board; American lobster up to 10
percent by weight of all other species on board or two hundred lobsters,
whichever is less; and skate and skate parts up to 10 percent by weight of all
other species on board.<p>

<b>Mid- Atlantic (MA) Regulated Mesh Area</b><p>
See Area definition in <a href="rmar.html">Fact Sheet 1</a><p>

Vessels fishing in the MA regulated mesh area are exempt from the 5% bycatch
criteria specifications and may, therefore, fish in a fishery outside of a DAS,
provided that they do not possess or land regulated multispecies finfish. <p>
<p>

