<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<h2 align=center>  Data Management Support Staff </h2>
<hr>

<blockquote>
<p>
<h3 align=center>Joan Palmer, Chief</h3><p>
The Data Management Support Staff assists the Northeast Fisheries Science
Center and the Northeast Regional Operations Office personnel in the
collection, transcription, analysis, and dissemination of data through
acquisition, maintenance, and use of computer hardware and software; the
development, maintenance, and use of computerized data bases; and computer
network management.<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<hr>
<h3>Data Management Support</h3>

CONTACT:  Joan Palmer NEFSC, Woods Hole Laboratory                                            
<p>
<b>OBJECTIVE</b><p>
<b></b><p>
Provide professional support in the development, maintenance, and use of
computing systems and techniques required by NEFSC and NERO staffs.  Emphasis
is on developing a capability for identifying existing data in the Northeast
and interrelating and accessing these data resources over the NMFS wide area
network (WAN).<p>
<p>
<p>
<b>ANTICIPATED ACTIVITIES IN FY96</b><p>
<p>
<ul>
<li>Develop and manage Northeast regional computing systems and provide
consulting services to users.

<li>Provide transcription and computer timesharing and management support for the
region.

<li>Redesign and enhance sea-sampling data-handling procedures.

<li>Maintain support for Financial Reporting System software.

<li>Complete conversion to IT95 computing environments.

<li>Implement the NOAA Regional Security Plan, assign security officers, and
<li>Continue Regional Data Base Management System development.
<li>Develop and maintain a regional data directory.

<li>Provide local area network (LAN) and WAN support for NEFSC.
</ul>

<b>ANTICIPATED PRODUCTS IN FY96</b>
<p>

<ul>
<li>Data for user groups.

<li>Data sets for "Status of Fishery Resources off the Northeastern United
States."

<li>Report of commercial fishery statistics for NMFS Headquarters and the North
Atlantic Fisheries Organization.

<li>LAN and WAN management for the NEFSC.

<li>Regional security plans for NEFSC LANs.

<li>Software applications to support data base development and maintenance.

<li>Regional data directory.
</ul>

</DOC>
