<body>
<font color="#003d84">
<center><h2>Current Research and Cooperative Studies</h2></center>
</font>
<p>
<hr>
<blockquote>The following is a brief list of research studies the staff of the Fishery Biology
Investigation are conducting.  
</blockquote>
<p>

<blockquote>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li>Conduct growth and maturation studies of winter flounder, ocean pout, longhorn sculpin,
redfish, and cusk.</li>
</ul>
<p>


<ul>
  <li>Conduct age validation and growth studies for white hake and scup.</li>
</ul>
<p>


<ul>
  <li>Continued participation in age structure exchanges with Canadian (Atlantic cod and haddock)
and other ageing laboratories.</li>
</ul>
<p>


<ul>
  <li>Study reproductive strategies and their contribution to gene flow and population recruitment
in longfin squid, <i>Loligo pealei</i> (cooperative research with MBL, WHOI, URI, Dalhousie
Univ.).</li>
</ul>
<p>


<ul>
  <li>Analyze migration and distribution patterns of Atlantic cod utilizing data from fish tagged in
1993.</li>
</ul>
<p>


<ul>
  <li>Conduct fecundity studies of haddock, winter flounder, and ocean pout.</li>
</ul>
<p>


<ul>
  <li>Examine the variability in juvenile winter flounder growth and survival in three habitats:
Milford, CT, Sandy Hook, NJ, and Tuckerton, NJ.</li>
</ul>
<p>


<ul>
  <li>Develop biochemical indices of maturity and egg quality in Atlantic cod.</li>
</ul>
<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>


