<title> NEFSC </title>
<BODY  bgcolor="#f8f8ff">
<blockquote>
<img align=right src="/labs/wh.jpg">
<h2>
Woods Hole Laboratory<br>
Northeast Fisheries Science Center<br>
National Marine Fisheries Service, NOAA<br>
</h2>
<h3>
166 Water Street<br>
Woods Hole, MA 02543-1026<br>
</h3>

Switchboard:  508-495-2000<br>
FAX:  Fax:  508-495-2258 508-495-2062 <br>
<p>
<p>
<b>Officer-in-Charge:  Dr. George Grice, (508) 495-2365</b>
<p>
     The Center Directorate, Research Planning and Coordination
Staff, Program Support Staff, Data Management Support Staff and
elements of the research Divisions are located at the Woods Hole
Laboratory.  The laboratory also houses a public and research
aquarium and is home port for two research vessels, the R/V
Albatross IV and R/V Delaware II.
<p>
The Woods Hole facility occupies 3.4 acres on Vineyard Sound. The facility at
Woods Hole houses both the Woods Hole
Laboratory and the Northeast Fisheries Center. The center provides overall
management and direction for the five laboratories
located in the Northeast Region.
<p>

