<HEAD>
   <TITLE>ACLU Press Release -  01/16/97 -- ACLU Decries Atlanta Bombings of Abortion Clinic</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="User-Agent: Mozilla/3.0Gold (Macintosh; I; PPC)">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF">

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/pressrel.gif" HEIGHT=54 WIDTH=572> </P>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>ACLU Decries Atlanta Bombings of Abortion Clinic</H2>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Statement of Catherine Weiss, <BR>
Director ACLU Reproductive Freedom Project</H3>

<P><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<BR>
Thursday, January 16, 1997</B></P>

<P>ATLANTA -- The American Civil Liberties Union is appalled by the two
bombings at the Atlanta Northside Family Planning Services this morning.
Our sympathies are with the people injured and with all the doctors and
clinics that have the courage to continue providing abortion services in
this atmosphere of unrelenting terror.</P>

<P>The explosions continue the rash of violence targeting abortion providers
across the nation. Last year, violence aimed at clinics occurred in more
than half the states and dozens of cities. </P>

<P>The ACLU -- a vigilant defender of free speech and the constitutional
right to reproductive choice -- reiterates that the First Amendment provides
no refuge for violence. Those who seek to stop abortions can express themselves
by the same means as everyone else, but like everyone else, they will be
criminally prosecuted when they resort to explosions to press their point.
The First Amendment does not provide immunity to violent vigilantes.</P>

<P>The ACLUs Reproductive Freedom Project helped to draft and lobby for
the Freedom of Access to Clinics Entrances Act, the 1994 federal law that
prohibits violence and obstruction aimed at interfering with the exercise
of reproductive rights. The law has proved to be a valuable tool against
anti-choice violence, and we continue to defend the law in court against
challenges to its constitutionality.</P>

<P>We urge other fair-minded Americans to join us in condemning todays
bombing and in expressing solidarity with its intended and actual victims.</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<CENTER><P><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG ISMAP SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=31 WIDTH=449></A>
</P></CENTER>

<H6 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Copyright 1996, The American Civil Liberties Union</I></H6>

