<H1>ACLU Press Releases</H1>
<H3>August Press Releases</H3>
<P><A NAME="cyber"></A><A HREF="n082396a.html">08/23/96 -- ACLU Responds to
Princeton &quot;Clarification&quot; of Internet Censorship Policy: End It, Don't
Mend It</A><BR>NEW YORK--The American Civil Liberties Union today criticized
Princeton University's &quot;clarification&quot; of its policy barring faculty,
students and staff from using the schools' computer network for &quot;political
purposes,&quot; calling on the university to rescind the ban.  </P>
<P><A NAME="free"></A><A HREF="n081596a.html">08/15/96 -- ACLU of Ohio Warns
Blue Cross/Blue Shield Attorney to Back Off Threats</A><BR>Critics of Sale Have
Right to Voice Opinions, ACLU Legal Director Says</P>
<P><A NAME="cyber"></A><A HREF="n081496a.html">08/15/96 -- Free Speech 101:
ACLU Gives Princeton University an &quot;F&quot; for Barring Political Speech on
its Network</A><BR>NEW YORK--In a letter sent today to Princeton University
officials,  the American Civil Liberties Union urged them to reconsider a policy
barring students and staff from using the Internet for &quot;political purposes.&quot;
</P>
<P><A NAME="reproductive"></A><A HREF="n081296a.html">08/12/96 -- ACLU Seeks
Injunction in Federal Court to Block Mississippi Abortion Statute and
Regulations</A><BR><B>Jackson, MS</B> -- A Mississippi pro-choice coalition
and two physicians filed a lawsuit today to stop state officials from enforcing
a new Statute and Regulations that threaten women's health and safety and
violate a number of constitutional guarantees, including the right to choose
abortion.</P>
<P><A NAME="free"></A><A HREF="n080896a.html">08/08/96 -- Court Orders City
to Pay ACLU of Ohio Attorney's Fees in Cincinnati Fountain Square Cross Case</A><BR>United
States District Judge Sandra Beckwith yesterday afternoon ordered the City of
Cincinnati to pay $46,728.48 as the attorney's fees of the American Civil
Liberties Union of Ohio in the lawsuit challenging the City's unconstitutional &quot;fighting
words&quot; ordinance.</P>
<P><A NAME="immigrants"></A><A HREF="n080596a.html">08/05/96 -- CA Youth
Embark on Field Investigation To Find Out 'What's Up' With Immigration</A><BR>SAN
FRANCISCO -- Later this week, 25 teenagers from throughout northern California
will embark on an investigation: &quot;Immigration: What's Up with That?&quot; 
Planned by and for youth and sponsored by the ACLU-NC Howard A. Friedman First
Amendment Education Project and Global Exchange, the eight-day educational
journey will explore the widely varying aspects of immigration by pursuing
first-hand knowledge of everything from border checks in San Diego to farm labor
in Watsonville.</P>
<P><A NAME="national"></A><A NAME="criminal"></A><A NAME="cyber"></A><A
HREF="n080296a.html">08/02/96 -- ACLU Applauds House on Restrained Terrorism
Measure; Anti-Liberty Wiretap Provisions Were Stripped</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- The

American Civil Liberties Union today applauded the House of Representatives for
stripping anti-liberty wiretapping measures from the counterterrorism
legislation approved this afternoon.</P>
<P><A NAME="aids"></A><A NAME="gay"></A><A HREF="n080196c.html">08/01/96 --
HIV 'Prevention' Bill Would Violate Rights  and Do More Harm Than Good</A><BR>WASHINGTON
-- The American Civil Liberties Union today summarily dismissed the so-called &quot;HIV
Prevention Act of 1996,&quot; saying it would violate important civil liberties
protections and jeopardize public safety by ignoring  guidelines
long-established by public health officials.  
</P>
<P><A NAME="racial"></A><A NAME="students"></A><A NAME="church"></A><A
HREF="n080196b.html">08/01/96 -- House Approves English-Only Legislation; ACLU
Says Bill Sends Wrong Message</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- The American Civil Liberties
Union today criticized the House of Representatives for passing an 
unconstitutional and mean-spirited bill that would bar the government from using
 any language but English. 
</P>
<P><A NAME="immigrants"></A><A NAME="church"></A><A NAME="national"></A><A
HREF="n080196a.html">08/01/96 -- ACLU Applauds Rep. Barr for Calling for Pause;
Says Counter-Terrorism Measures Endanger Liberties</A><BR>WASHINGTON &#150; The
American Civil Liberties Union today applauded Representative Bob Barr and his
colleagues for urging that Congress act slowly on so-called counter-terrorism
measures.</P>
<P><A NAME="church"></A><A HREF="n080196d.html">08/01/96 -- ACLU, Rights
Groups Vow to Fight School Voucher Ruling</A><BR>The ruling on school vouchers
issued by Franklin County Common Pleas Court Judge Lisa Sadler on July 31 is a
disappointment to all opposed to diverting tax dollars to private schools. There
is no question the ruling will be appealed.</P>
