<TITLE>ACLU Press Release -- July Press Releases</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/newshdr.gif">
<P></P>
<H1>ACLU Press Releases</H1>
<H3>July Press Releases</H3>
<P><A NAME="cyber"></A><A HREF="n073196a.html">07/31/96 -- ACLU Warns of
Latest Government Efforts to Regulate Cyberspace; New Global Campaign Will
Monitor National, International Threats</A><BR>NEW YORK, NY--Despite a second
federal court decision affirming that censorship in cyberspace is
unconstitutional, the ACLU today warned of  persistent government attempts, in
the U.S. and internationally, to censor electronic communications and regulate
privacy technology.   </P>
<P><A NAME="gay"></A><A NAME="workplace"></A><A HREF="n073096a.html">07/30/96
-- ACLU Says Government and Private Groups Operating Boy Scout Troops Are
Discriminating</A><BR>CHICAGO -- Charging that the City of Chicago, the Chicago
Board of Education, the FBI, Commonwealth Edison, and other government and
private organizations are participating in illegal discrimination by operating
Boy Scout units, the American Civil Liberties Union today announced that it has
demanded that these organizations either seek to change the Boy Scouts'
discriminatory practices or stop participating in the local scouting council. 
</P>
<P><A NAME="national"></A><A NAME="privacy"></A><A HREF="n072996b.html">07/29/96
-- ACLU Publishes &quot;Your Free Speech Rights During the  Republican
Convention,&quot; Announces Free Speech Hotline</A><BR>The ACLU of San Diego
and Imperial Counties this weekend began distributing 15,000 copies of &quot;Your
Free Speech Rights During the Republican Convention.&quot;  The 2-page flier in
Q&amp;A format is a general guide for demonstrators, marchers, speakers and
others who plan to exercise their First Amendment rights during convention week,
August 12-15, in San Diego.  	</P>

<P><A NAME="cyber"></A><A NAME="national"></A><A HREF="n072996a.html">07/29/96

-- ACLU Calls for Meeting with President, Congress  To Put Brakes on Expansion

of Wiretapping</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- In a letter to President Clinton and
Congressional leaders, the American Civil Liberties Union today asked for a
meeting to express civil liberties concerns about the new proposals to expand
still further federal wiretapping authority.  
</P>
<P><A NAME="church"></A><A NAME="reproductive"></A><A NAME="immigrants"></A><A
HREF="n072696c.html">07/26/96 -- Unconstitutional Welfare Bill Preys on Our
Nation's Children  Measure Also Erodes Free Speech, Violates Separation of
Church, State and Damages Privacy Rights</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- Scrambling to
finalize its third version of a welfare &quot;reform&quot; bill, Congress has
refused to discard portions that prey upon the innocence and vulnerability of
children, immigrants, the poor and the elderly. 
</P>
<P><A NAME="students"></A><A HREF="n072696b.html">07/26/96 -- Partial
Settlement in Oakland School Uniform Lawsuit;   Board Will Notify Parents About

Uniform Financial Aid, Opt Out</A><BR>In a step that will help to ensure
fairness for all Oakland K-8 students, the Oakland Unified School District Board
has agreed to a multi-faceted plan for informing parents about their rights
under the new state law governing school uniforms, and for providing families
with financial assistance.</P>
<P><A NAME="workplace"></A><A HREF="n072696a.html">07/26/96 -- Northwestern
to Expand Services for Non-English Speakers</A><BR>MILWAUKEE -- The
Northwestern Mutual Life Insurance Company and a group of public interest law
firms, including the American Civil Liberties Union of Northern California, the
Mexican American Legal Defense and Education Fund and The Employment Law Center,
today announce the settlement of a class action lawsuit.  As part of that
agreement, Northwestern has introduced a number of new services to assist its
agents in marketing the company's products to non-English speaking individuals. 

</P>
<P><A NAME="reproductive"></A><A HREF="n072596a.html">07/25/96 -- ACLU
Condemns Welfare Bill; Urges  Clinton to Veto</A><BR>The American Civil
Liberties Union strongly condemned welfare legislation passed by both the House
and Senate and called for President Clinton's veto. In addition to punishing

children and legal immigrants by denying them much needed benefits, both bills

violate constitutionally protected speech, religious liberty, and equal
protection rights.</P>
<P><A HREF="n072396a.html"> 07/23/96 -- ACLU Files Class Action Lawsuit 
Challenging Anti-begging Law</A><BR>DENVER -- The American Civil Liberties
Union of Colorado filed a lawsuit today in federal court to challenge the
constitutionality of a Colorado statute that makes it a crime to loiter &quot;with
the purpose of begging.&quot;  
</P>
<P><A NAME="security"></A><A HREF="n072296b.html"> 07/22/96 -- ACLU Applauds
Hyde for Efforts on Asset Forfeiture; Testifies Before House Judiciary Committee</A><BR>WASHINGTON--
Citing a &quot;parade of horribles,&quot; the American Civil Liberties Union 
today urged Congress to overhaul the civil asset forfeiture system in the United
 States.</P>

<P><A NAME="church"></A><A HREF="n072296a.html">07/22/96 -- ACLU Vigorously
Opposes Attempt By  Gingrich and Armey to Amend The Bill of Rights</A><BR>WASHINGTON--The
American Civil Liberties Union today said that it vigorously opposed a

Constitutional amendment to the religion clauses of the First Amendment
sponsored by House Majority Leader Dick Armey (R-TX).</P>
<P><A NAME="free"></A><A HREF="n071996d.html">07/19/96 -- Judge Rules
Unconstitutional GOP Effort To Block Free Speech At San Diego Convention</A><BR>SAN
DIEGO -- In a ruling that will dramatically bolster the right to free speech at 
future political conventions, Federal Judge Rudi Brewster today struck down
plans by the Republican National Committee to limit free speech outside the San
Diego Convention Center during the week of the Republican National Convention.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n071996c.html">07/19/96 -- ACLU Mourns Loss of Stephen Donaldson,
President of Stop Prisoner Rape, ACLU v. Reno Plaintiff 
</A><BR> NEW YORK -- The ACLU was saddened to learn of the death of Stephen &quot;Donny&quot;
Donaldson, president of Stop Prisoner Rape, Inc.  Donaldson, a longtime advocate
on behalf of survivors of jailhouse rape, died on Thursday, July 18, in New York
City.
</P>
<P><A NAME="students"></A><A HREF="n071996b.html">07/19/96 -- KT City Curfew
Declared Unconstitutional; Federal Court Blocks Henderson Measure</A><BR>A
federal court has declared the City of Henderson's juvenile curfew law to be
unconstitutional and has permanently enjoined its enforcement.  In a decision
issued June 27, 1996, U.S. District Judge Joseph H. McKinley states that the
ordinance &quot;broadly stifles fundamental personal liberties.&quot;          
</P>
<P><A NAME="reproductive"></A><A HREF="n071996a.html">07/19/96 -- ACLU Urges
FDA to Approve Mifepristone for Early Medical Abortion: Statement of Janet
Gallagher, Director ACLU's Reproductive Freedom Project</A><BR>WASHINGTON --
For more than a decade, American women have been denied the option of safe and
effective nonsurgical abortions because of vocal protests from anti-choice
extremists.  The Food and  Drug Administration now has the opportunity to
approve Mifepristone, and provide women with an important new option of early
medical abortions. 
</P>
<P><A NAME="free"></A><A HREF="n071896a.html">07/18/96 -- ACLU Negotiates For
Free Expression Forums During Democratic  Convention; Halts City's Plan to
Stifle Expression
</A><BR> CHICAGO -- Following months of negotiations with the City of Chicago
and the Chicago Park District, the American Civil Liberties Union of Illinois

today announced that it has reached an agreement to ensure that everyone is
allowed to exercise First Amendment rights when the Democratic National
Convention meets here next month.</P>
<P><A NAME="church"></A><A HREF="n071696d.html">07/16/96 -- ACLU Condemns
Effort to Alter The Constitution's Religion Clauses</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- The
American Civil Liberties Union today strongly condemned renewed Congressional
efforts to amend the Constitution in a way that could destroy our nation's
205-year heritage of government neutrality toward religion and individual
religious beliefs.</P>
<P><A HREF="n071696c.html">07/16/96 -- ACLU Blasts Judiciary Committee's
Extremist Agenda; Says Bills on Voting Rights, Juvenile Justice and Minority
Business Demonstrate Intolerance</A><BR>WASHINGTON ' Surveying the pre-election
agenda of the House Judiciary Committee, the American Civil Liberties Union
today accused the committee and its leaders of pursuing an agenda of intolerance
and divisiveness.</P>
<P><A NAME="security"></A><A HREF="n071696b.html">07/16/96 -- ACLU Calls on
Congress To Kick Wiretap Habit And Eliminate 'Stealth Funding' For Digital
Telephony</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- Calling on Congress to kick the government's
increasingly expensive wiretap habit, the ACLU today decried what it called &quot;stealth
 funding&quot; for digital telephony wiretapping in the House appropriations
bill  for the Departments of Commerce, Justice and State.</P>
<P><A NAME="students"></A><A NAME="security"></A><A HREF="n071696a.html">07/16/96
-- ACLU Criticizes H.R. 3565, &quot;The Violent Youth Predator Act of 1996&quot;
</A><BR>WASHINGTON, DC-- The so-called &quot;Youth Predator Act,&quot; up for
consideration before the House Judiciary Committee today, is perhaps the logical
 result of all the inflammatory rhetoric on juvenile crime that we have heard at
louder and louder volume since the beginning of this election year.  </P>
<P><A NAME="gay"></A><A HREF="n071296a.html">07/12/96 -- ACLU Condemns House
Passage of the Anti-Gay Marriage Bill, Says Measure is Unconstitutional and Bad
Public Policy</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- The American Civil Liberties Union today
condemned many of its traditional allies in House, including stalwart civil 
rights leaders, for passing the so-called &quot;Defense of Marriage Act,&quot;
which would deny recognition of marriages between lesbian and gay couples.</P>
<P><A NAME="students"></A><A HREF="n071196c.html">07/11/96 -- ACLUF, Student
Editor Hail California  Supreme Court Ruling Allowing Lawsuit Against Gov.
Wilson, Regents For Violation of State Open Meeting Act to Proceed</A><BR>LOS
ANGELES - The ACLU Foundation of Southern California and student plaintiff Tim
Molloy hailed the California Supreme Court decision of July 10 refusing to
review the California Court of Appeal ruling last May which said a suit against
the UC Regents for violating the California Open Meeting Act will go forward.</P>
<P><A HREF="n071196b.html">07/11/96 -- ACLU of Maryland Announces Appointment
of New Executive Director</A><BR>BALTIMORE -- The Board of Governors of the
Maryland ACLU tonight announced the appointment of Susan Goering to succeed
outgoing Executive Director Stuart Comstock-Gay.  Goering has served as the
organization's Legal Director since 1987, and will assume her new position on 
July 20.</P>
<P><A NAME="gay"></A><A HREF="n071196a.html">07/11/96 -- ACLU Criticizes
Allies for Jumping Ship on Gay Marriage; Submits Testimony Calling Bill
Unconstitutional, Bad Public Policy</A><BR>WASHINGTON -- As a Senate committee
examined a bill that would deny recognition of marriages between lesbian and gay
couples, the American Civil Liberties Union criticized many of its traditional
allies, including stalwart civil rights activists, for jumping ship on this
issue of fundamental fairness.</P>
<P><A NAME="criminal"></A><A HREF="n070996c.html">07/09/96 -- ACLU White
Paper Says LAPD Fails Citizen Complaint Process Called for By 1991 Christopher
Commission Report</A><BR>LOS ANGELES -- The ACLU of Southern California
released a white paper today detailing shortcomings the Los Angeles Police
Department's citizen complaint process, which the ACLU studied in 1992 and about
which the Christopher Commission was extremely critical in its 1991 report
prompted by the beating of Rodney King by LAPD police officers. </P>
<P><A NAME="racial"></A><A HREF="n070996b.html">07/09/96 -- CT Supreme Court
Rules That Racial and Ethnic Segregation In Hartford Area Schools Violates State
Constitution</A><BR>HARTFORD -- In an historic decision, the Connecticut
Supreme Court today ruled that the condition of racial and ethnic segregation in
the Hartford metropolitan area deprives schoolchildren of their fundamental
rights under the state constitution to an equal educational opportunity:  &quot;Racial
and ethnic segregation has a pervasive and invidious impact on schools, whether
the segregation results from intentional conduct or from unorchestrated
demographic factors.&quot; 
</P>
<P><A NAME="cyber"></A><A HREF="n070596a.html">07/05/96 --ACLU To Challenge
New State Law  Restricting Internet Use; Civil Liberties Group Says Academic
Freedom in Virginia at Stake</A><BR>RICHMOND -- The ACLU of Virginia announced
today that it will soon challenge in court the constitutionality of a new law
prohibiting state employees from accessing sexually explicit materials on the
Internet.  The ACLU says the state has the right to limit use of its computers
to state business but that it cannot curtail academic freedom in the process.</P>
<P><A NAME="gay"></A><A HREF="n070196a.html">07/01/96 -- Ruling on &quot;Don't
Ask, Don't Tell&quot; Ban on Gay Troops Kicked Back to Federal District Court: 
Federal Appeals Court Focuses on Equal Treatment Issues Raised by Lambda and
ACLU </A><BR>NEW YORK --  A federal appeals court today sent back a challenge
to the Pentagon's two-year-old &quot;Don't Ask, Don't Tell&quot; law and ruled
that a lower court must decide whether the constitution allows the government to
treat lesbians and gay men in the military differently than non-gay
servicemembers.</P>
<P></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
