<TITLE>ACLU Press Release -- May 1996 Press Releases</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/newshdr.gif">
<P></P>
<CENTER></CENTER>
<H1></H1>
<CENTER>ACLU Press Releases</CENTER>
<P></P>
<H3>May 1996 Press Releases  </H3>
<P><A HREF="n053196a.html">5/31/96 -- MI Agrees to Send Voter Registration
Forms As Part of Court-Ordered Remedy</A><BR> In settlement of an ACLU lawsuit,
the state of Michigan has started to mail voter registration applications to
more than a million potential new Michigan voters.</P>
<P><A HREF="n053096a.html">5/30/96 -- ACLU Says National Curfew Policy &quot;Ain't
No Cure for the Summertime Blues&quot;</A><BR>President Clinton's announcement
today of support for a national curfew policy is more than another reason for
the summertime blues for teenagers.  Their rights are being taken away in broad
daylight with no measurable return in public safety.</P>
<P><A HREF="n052296.html">5/22/96 -- ACLU Calls Proposal to Drug Test Welfare
Recipients a &quot;False Positive&quot;</A><BR>Bob Dole's proposal  to require
all welfare recipients to submit to drug tests may sound like a  positive
solution to some, but the results would be totally false to the  ideals of
democracy in America.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n052296a.html">5/22/96 -- ACLU Says that Clinton  Limits on
Affirmative Action Ignore Evidence of Continuing and Persistent  Discrimination
</A><BR>Although it said that it has found evidence of &quot;very real, 
ongoing impact of discrimination,&quot; the Clinton Administration today 
proposed new limits on affirmative action programs that help minorities to 
competitively bid on federal contracts. 
</P>
<P><A HREF="n052296b.html">5/22/96 -- ACLU Says Vacco's Pact with  Glorious
Food is a Sham; ACLU's Class Action Proceeds Undisturbed 
</A><BR>NEW YORK -- The American Civil Liberties Union today criticized an 
agreement by New York State Attorney General Dennis Vacco that seeks to resolve
sex  bias claims made against Glorious Food -- one of the city's most
prestigious  catering companies. 
</P>
<P><A HREF="n052296c.html">5/22/96 -- ACLU Says That Clinton  Panders to
Bigotry With Announcement That He Will Sign Ban on Same-Sex  Marriage</A><BR>The
American Civil Liberties Union today urgently requested that the Clinton 
Administration rethink its support for legislation that would ban same-sex 
marriages.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n052096b.html">5/20/96 -- ACLU APPLAUDS SUPREME COURT  DECISION
STRIKING DOWN COLORADO'S ANTI-GAY AMENDMENT 2</A><BR>Today's  decision marks a
sea change in the struggle of lesbian and gay men for equality in America.  The
ruling makes the promise of  Equal Protection a reality for lesbian, gay and
bisexual Americans.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n052096a.html">5/20/96 -- OREGON ACLU SAYS SUPREME  COURT DECISION
IS &quot;DEATH KNELL&quot; FOR OCA MEASURE</A><BR>Today's decision by the  U.S.
Supreme Court which overturned Colorado's Amendment 2 should be the death knell

for the OCA's &quot;Daughter of 13.&quot;
</P>
<P><A HREF="n051696.html">5/16/96 -- ACLU Opposes Unconstitutional  Bill That
Would Prohibit Alcohol Advertising</A><BR>The American Civil  Liberties Union
today said that it strongly opposed a bill introduced today  by Rep. Joseph
Kennedy, D-MA, that would violate constitutionally  protected commercial speech
rights -- rights the Supreme Court &amp;nbsp; reaffirmed just  this week.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n051596.html">5/15/96 -- ACLU Submits Statement Before  House
Anti-Gay Marriage Hearing; Says Legislation is Unnecessary,  Unprecedented and
Unconstitutional</A><BR>The American Civil Liberties submitted  a statement
today before a House subcommittee hearing on a bill that would  outlaw marriages
between lesbian and gay couples, calling the bill &quot;a  deplorable act of
hostility unworthy of the United States Congress.&quot;
</P>
<P><A HREF="n051396.html">5/13/96 -- ACLU Testifies at  Congressional Black
Caucus Braintrust on Youth Violence: &amp;nbsp;What Ever Happened to  Prevention<BR>
</A>The American Civil Liberties Union, leading criminologists, community
activists and others will present testimony tomorrow  (Tuesday, May 14th) at the
Congressional Black Caucus Braintrust on Youth  Violence, a day-long hearing
that will examine the overlooked solution to  juvenile crime: prevention. 
</P>
<P><A HREF="n051096a.htm">5/10/96 -- ACLU v. Reno Trial Update--  AT CLOSING
ARGUMENTS, ACLU CALLS ON COURT TO PROTECT FREE SPEECH IN CYBERSPACE</A><BR>A
three-judge panel heard closing arguments  today regarding a law that would
criminalize free speech in cyberspace.  Plaintiffs  and defendants each had
approximately two hours to make their case and answer questions from the judges.
 
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050996.htm">5/09/96 -- Appeals Court to HearArguments  In Case on
24-Hour Wait for Abortions</A><BR>The Michigan Court of Appeals  will hear oral
arguments, May 9, 1996 in the ACLU challenge to the state's  attempt to require
a 24-hour mandatory waiting period and biased counseling and materials for women
seeking  abortions.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050996b.html"> 05/09/96 -- ACLU Director Authors &quot;Do-It-Yourself&quot;
Guidebook for New Era in Gay Rights Struggle</A><BR>Fed with up being treated
as a second-class citizen?  Do you want your town to outlaw sexual orientation
discrimination?  Want your town to recognize domestic partnerships? Matt Coles,
Director of the ACLU's Lesbian and Gay Rights Project, has the answers in a new
book: Try This At Home! </P>
<P><A HREF="n050896.htm">5/08/96 -- ACLU v. Reno: A  CHRONOLOGY</A><BR>At a
news conference in Washington, D.C., the ACLU announces plans to seek a 
temporary restraining order against indecency provisions of the
Telecommunications Bill immediately after it is signed into law by  President
Clinton on February 8.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050896b.htm">5/08/96 -- ACLU Says Anti-Gay Marriage Bill is an
Unprecedented Intrusion on State Issue</A><BR>The American Civil Liberties
Union questioned a bill introduced today that  would ban marriages between
lesbian and gay couples, saying that Congress is  inappropriately intruding on a
state issue.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050896a.htm">5/08/96 -- ACLU v. Reno Update --Closing  Arguments
Heard Friday, May 10</A><BR>Wrapping up five days of courtroom testimony before
a three-judge panel in federal district court in  Philadelphia, the ACLU will
present closing arguments this Friday, May 10, in the trial that will determine 
the future of free speech in cyberspace.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050296.htm">5/02/96 -- ACLU Calls Senate Immigration  Bill &quot;Unconstitutional,

Unwise and Un-American&quot;</A><BR>The Senate today  approved  the most
wide-ranging immigration proposals in decades, legislation that the ACLU called 
&quot;unconstitutional,unwise and un-American.&quot;      
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050196.html">5/01/96 -- ACLU Honored for &quot;Excellence  in
Internet Promotion&quot; at Internet World Conference</A><BR>The American Civil
 Liberties Union received an award April 30 for &quot;Excellence in Promotion of
the  Internet&quot; from Internet industry publisher Mecklermedia Corporation at
its Spring  '96  Internet World Conference in San Jose, California.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050196a.htm">5/01/96 -- ACLU Condemns Legislation That Strips
Soldiers' Rights</A><BR>The American Civil Liberties Union  strongly condemned
an amendment that was approved in a House Committee  today, saying that it would
gut the First Amendment rights of American soldiers  stationed around the globe.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050196b.htm">5/01/96 -- ACLU Criticizes AIDS Funding Bill Phasing
in Mandatory Testing of Babies</A><BR>Saying Congress is making  bad public
health policy and damaging civil liberties in one stroke, the  American Civil 
Liberties Union today criticized a provision agreed upon by House and Senate
conferees  that would eventually require states to begin mandatory testing of
newborns  for HIV.
</P>
<P><A HREF="n050196c.htm">5/01/96 -- ACLU Files Lawsuit Against Conway Public
Schools On Behalf Of Students Who Were Strip-Searched</A><BR>The ACLU of
Arkansas filed a lawsuit in  federal court today on behalf of Conway High School
students who were  strip searched by school officials on April 24, 1996. 
</P>

