<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ACLU Press Release -- Current Press Releases</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<blockquote>

<IMG SRC="/graphics/newshdr.gif"><P>

<center><h1>ACLU Press Releases</h1></center>
<P>

<h3>April Press Releases</h3>

<a href="n042996b.html">4/29/96 -- Supreme Court Rejects SD Abortion Law</a><br>Planned Parenthood Federation of America (PPFA) and the
American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) today applauded the U.S. Supreme
Court's decision to let stand a lower court ruling striking down a South
Dakota abortion law. 
<p>


<a href="n042996.html">4/29/96 -- ACLU OF Pennsylvania Selects
Larry Frankel As New Executive Director</a><br>This selection is actually a promotion because Frankel has been the Legislative Director of the ACLU of Pennsylvania since the fall of 1992.
<p>

<a href="n042596b.html">4/25/96 -- Judge to Hear Death Penalty Arguments</a><br> U.S. District Court Judge Vaughn Walker will hear oral arguments on April 30 in an ACLU case filed on behalf of journalists challenging the state's use of secret execution procedures.
<p>

<a href="n042596.html">4/25/96 -- Congress Repleals Ban on HIV-Positive Troops</a><br>The ACLU today commended
congressional leaders for agreeing to repeal legislation that would
have forced the Defense Department to discharge service members who
tested positive for HIV, calling the move a historic step towards
fairness for people living with the virus.
<p>

<a href="n042496.html">4/24/96 -- Clinton's Legacy: The Great Writ is Crippled</a><br>With the stroke of a pen, President Clinton today crippled
the century-old authority of the federal courts to enforce the Bill of
Rights.
<p>

<a href="n042296.html">4/22/96 -- ACLU Criticizes Congressional Hearings to 
          Examine Scope of Roe v. Wade</a><br>The American Civil Liberties Union today criticized
congressional hearings to examine the scope of Roe v. Wade, saying that
anti-choice extremists in the House are trying to lay the groundwork for
overturning a women's constitutional right to choose abortion.
<p>

<a href="n041996.html">4/19/96 -- CA Court Asked to Reconsider Abortion Ruling</a><br>In response to the California Supreme Court's April 4 ruling
in American Academy of Pediatrics v. Lungren, upholding a statute restricting minors' access to abortion by requiring parental or judicial consent, the ACLU-NC is filing a petition today asking the Court to rehear the case.
<p>
<a href="n041896c.html">4/18/96 --  NYCLU Files Suit
Challenging Removal of DA in Death Penalty Case</a><br>The New York Civil Liberties Union (NYCLU) today is filing, on behalf of five
Bronx County voters and taxpayers, a lawsuit challenging Governor Pataki's
superseding of Bronx District Attorney Robert Johnson in the case of the March
14, 1996 killing of New York City Police Officer Kevin Gillespie.<p>

<a href="n041896b.html">4/18/96 -- Rights Trampled as Terror Bill Passes</a><br>In an open letter to President Clinton, the American Civil
Liberties Union today called on the President to reject the terrorism bill
and preserve the authority of the federal courts to enforce the Bill of
Rights.
<p>
<a href="n041896.html">4/18/96 -- Utah ACLU Vows Gay Ban Challenge</a><br>Utah legislatures voted late Wednesday evening to pass a controversial
bill designed to bar lesbian and gay student clubs while allowing
other groups to form.
<p>
<a href="n041796c.html">4/17/96 -- Wrongly Accused Oklahoma City Suspect Rejects
     Government's Token Settlement Offer 
</a><br>A Jordanian-American who was wrongly detained one year ago for the Oklahoma City bombing today rejected a token settlement offer by the Justice Department, saying the government is failing to take his claims seriously. 

<p>
<a href="n041796b.html">4/17/96 -- Wiretap Still in Terrorism Bill</a><br>The American Civil Liberties Union today alerted  members of
the House of Representatives that significant wiretap provisions remain in
the terrorism legislation now making its way through Congress.
<p>
<a href="n041796.html">4/17/96 --Utah Lawmakers Ban Gay Clubs</a><br>Seeking to sidestep a federal law guaranteeing equal access
in the schools,  Utah lawmakers will hold a special legislative session today
to vote on a controversial bill aimed at restricting
lesbian and gay student clubs while allowing all other extracurricular
clubs to meet.
<p>
<a href="n041596b.html">4/15/96 -- ACLU v. Reno: Trial Update</a><br>Testifying on the last day of trial in ACLU v. Reno, government witness Dan Olsen told a three-judge panel that the best way to comply with the censorship law would be to block all possibly "indecent" words and images, until "questionable" material could be reviewed and labeled for adult consumption.
<p>
<a href="n041596.html">4/15/96 -- Terrorism Bill Marks Watershed</a><br>Saying that Congress was on the verge of making fundamental decisions about how our democracy will function in the next century, the ACLU today strongly urged that House and Senate conferees reject President Clinton's call for counter terrorism legislation that would gut the Bill of Rights.
<p>
<a href="n041296.html">4/12/96 -- ACLU v. Reno: Trial Update</a><br>Testifying for the government today, Special Agent Howard A. Schmidt acknowledged, in answer to skeptical questioning by a three-judge panel, that it is "highly unlikely" for anyone to come across sexually explicit sites on the Internet by accident. 
<p>
<a href="n041196.html">4/11/96 -- ACLU Lauds Presidential Veto
Of Bill Banning Abortion Technique</a><br>"We applaud President Clinton for rejecting this unprecedented and inappropriate attempt by members of Congress to step into the operating room and legislate against specific medical procedures," said Janet Gallagher,
Director of the ACLU Reproductive Freedom Project.  
<p>
<a href="n041096b.html">4/10/96 -- Background Briefing, Juvenile Justice in America
</a><br>As House Republicans today convened the second in a series of
field hearings on juvenile crime, the ACLU warned that "get tough" laws are
making society more dangerous and writing off future generations. 
<p>
<a href="n041096.html">4/10/96 -- ACLU Statement on Juvenile Justice
</a><br>In this election year, politicians have once again focused
their attention on the issue of crime in America.  But this year, the
scapegoat is not Willie Horton -- it is our children.
<p>
<a href="n040996.html">4/9/96 --  ACLU Speaks Out on Juvenile Justice
</a><br>The ACLU will host a media availability tomorrow at a congressional field hearing in Atlanta that youth advocates charge is a smoke-screen for a Republican-led effort to dismantle the juvenile justice system.
<p>
<a href="n040896.html">4/8/96 --  Baltimore Housing Case Reaches Settlement
</a><br>The ACLU of Maryland today
announced its agreement to a housing plan that resolves the ACLU's
discrimination complaints concerning racial segregation in
Baltimore's high rise public housing.
<p>
<a href="n040596.html">4/5/96 --  U.S. Appeals Court Upholds Discharge of Gay Naval Officer; ACLU Says Ruling Ignores Core Issue in Case
</a><br>A divided federal appeals court upheld
the Pentagon's two-year old law barring lesbian and gay men from
openly serving in the military.
<p>
<a href="n040496.html">4/4/96 --  Government Calls Two Witnesses;  
MIT Expert Will Testify for Plaintiffs on PICS Standards
</a><br>Government lawyers today notified the ACLU that they plan to call
two witnesses in the next two days of hearings to determine the future of
 free speech in cyberspace.
<p>
<a href="n040296.html">4/2/96 --  ACLU Calls for Federal Probe into Police Beatings 
</a><br> The American Civil Liberties Union has called for an immediate federal Justice
Department investigation in response to the brutal beating of suspected illegal immigrants by Riverside County sheriffs. 
<p>
<a href="n040296b.html">4/2/96 --  ACLU Condemns Police Beating of Immigrants; Warns that
Immig. Bills Would Open Doors to More Abuses</a><br> The ACLU condemned the beating of two suspected undocumented immigrants by local police officers in El Monte, Calif., and warned that the immigration bills currently before Congress would open the doors to more human rights abuses. 
<p>
<a href="n040296c.html">4/2/96 --  Treasury Panel Targets Off-Duty Behavior; ACLU Says
Proposed Regulations Target the Constitution</a><br> The American Civil Liberties Union today raised serious objections to the Treasury Department's proposed regulations regarding off-duty conduct of agents. 
<p>

<a href="n040196b.html">4/1/96 --  Supreme Court Agrees to Hear Mississippi Mother's Case</a><br>The United States Supreme Court today agreed to hear a
challenge to a Mississippi Supreme Court practice that prevents indigent
citizens from filing appeals in civil court cases. 
<p>
<a href="n040196.html">4/1/96 --  ACLU v. Reno: Trial Update</a><br>You can't put a price on free speech in cyberspace, ACLU
Associate Director Barry Steinhardt told a three-judge panel in the final day
of plaintiff testimony in the group's legal challenge to Internet censorship.
<p>

