<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ACLU Press Release -- March Press Releases</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<blockquote>

<IMG SRC="/graphics/newshdr.gif"><P>

<center><h1>ACLU Press Releases</h1></center>
<P>

<h3>March Press Releases</h3>

<a href="n032896.html">3/28/96 --  ACLU Raises Questions About Clinton's
"One Strike and You're Out" Policy in Public Housing</a><br> The ACLU questioned
President Clinton's  "one strike and you're out" order to deny public housing
to those suspected of engaging in illegal activities.
<p>


<a href="n032796.html">3/27/96 --  ACLU Files Class Action Lawsuit Against Pittsburgh Over Police
Misconduct</a><br> The ACLU of Pennsylvania this morning filed a class action, civil
rights lawsuit against the City of Pittsburgh seeking to eradicate an historic and pervasive pattern of police
misconduct. 
<p>

<a href="n032796b.html">3/27/96 --  ACLU Condemns House Passage of Bill Banning Late-Term Abortion Procedure</a><br>The ACLU strongly condemned the House of Representatives for passing the Senate's version of
the so-called "Partial Birth Abortion Ban Act," a bill that criminalizes a
rarely used late-term abortion procedure.
<p>

<a href="n032296.html">3/22/96 --  First Two Days of Trial in
Battle for Free Speech in Cyberspace</a><br>In the first two days of trial in the battle for free speech
in cyberspace,  a three-judge panel heard testimony from plaintiffs who fear
censorship under the new telecommunications law and took a first-ever live
courtroom tour of the Internet.
<p>

<a href="n032196.html">3/21/96 --  ACLU Warns of First Amendment Concerns
in Military's Study on Extremist Activities</a><br>The ACLU expressed deep concern about a
U.S. Army task force report released by the Pentagon today that concluded
that the Army must "identify and address indications of extremist and racist
attitudes among soldiers."
<p>

<a href="n032096c.html">3/20/96 -- Citing Gay Rights Law, Connecticut High Court Upholds Ban on
Military Recruiting at University</a><br>Connecticut's highest court upheld a ban on military recruitment at the University
     of Connecticut School of Law, ruling that the Pentagon's "don't ask, don't tell" policy on lesbians and gay men
     violates the state's human rights law barring discrimination based on sexual orientation. 
<p>

<a href="n031496.html">3/14/96 -- Divided House Passes Anti-Terrorism Legislation;
ACLU Says Passage Marks Sad Day For Civil Liberties</a><br>The House of Representatives today approved legislation that
jeopardizes personal freedom and civil liberties in the name of fighting
crime and terrorism.<p>

<a href="n031396b.html">3/13/96 -- Revised House Anti-Terrorism Bill Threaten Civil Liberties; 
      ACLU Urges Representatives to Defeat Legislation</a><BR>
Reacting to the passage of the Barr Amendment to the
anti-terrorism legislation, the American Civil Liberties Union today warned
that the revised bill now being considered continues to threaten personal
freedom and civil liberties in the name of fighting terrorism.<p>

<a href="n031396.html">3/13/96 -- ACLU Says Religious Liberty Sidelined
In Suspension of Basketball Star</a><BR>
In suspending star  player Mahmoud Abdul-Rauf  for his refusal to stand
during the playing of the national anthem, the National Basketball
Association has sidelined religious liberty as well.<p>

<a href ="n031296b.html">3/12/96 -- ACLU Calls On President Clinton
To Show Continued Leadership on Affirmative Action</a><BR>
With the national media awash with conflicting leaks from the
Clinton Administration, the American Civil Liberties Union has urged
President Clinton not to stray from the impassioned defense of affirmative
action he delivered last year.<p>

<a href="n031296.html">3/12/96 -- House Leadership Maneuvers on Anti-Terrorism Bill
Continues To Threaten Civil Liberties</a><BR>
Reacting to furious maneuvering by House Republicans as a
critical floor vote nears, the American Civil Liberties Union today warned
that the anti-terrorism legislation now being discussed continues to threaten
personal freedom and civil liberties in the name of fighting terrorism.<p>

<a href="n030696.html">3/6/96 -- Lawsuit Filed By Former Employees
Charging Violation of Freedom of Association/Freedom of Speech By New York City
Board of Elections</a><BR>
The New York Civil Liberties Union (NYCLU) today filed, on
behalf of five former employees, a civil rights action alleging that the
conduct of the Board of Elections has infringed and continues to infringe
their freedom of association/freedom of speech rights.<p>

<a href="n030596b.html">3/5/96 -- Lawsuit Filed By  Saint of the City' Charging Violation
Of Free Speech Rights Against Mayor Giuliani.</a><BR>
The New York Civil Liberties Union (NYCLU) today filed, on
behalf of Rafael Sencion (who New York Newsday in May 1995 called the "Saint
of the City"), a civil rights action alleging that the conduct of defendant
officials of the City of New York has infringed and continues to infringe Mr.
Sencion's free speech rights.<p>

<a href="n030596.html">3/5/96 -- So-called Counterterrorism Bill Moving;
Rules Committee Sets Clock Ticking to Floor Debate</a><br>Despite continuing widespread national concern about the powers granted to federal law enforcement, the House Rules Committee today started
the clock toward floor consideration of the so-called antiterrorism act.<p>

<a href="n030496c.html">3/4/96 -- Mississippi Mother's School Prayer Challenge Goes to Trial</a>
<br>Trial begins today in a major school prayer case brought by a Mississippi mother seeking to stop unconstitutional and coercive religious practices in her children's public school.<p>

<a href="n030196.html">3/1/96 -- Gay Naval Officer's Case Will Be Argued
Before U.S. Appeals Court on March 4th</a><br>A challenge to the Pentagon's two-year-old "don't ask,
don't tell" policy on lesbians and gay men in the military will be heard on
Monday, March 4 <p>

<CENTER><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A><P>
