<center><h1> ACLU Press Releases</h1></center><P><h3>January 1996</h3>

<a href="n013096.html">1/30 --  Federal Court Strikes Down Alabama Law 
Barring Gay Student Groups from Campus</a> A federal court struck down an Alabama statute designed to bar lesbian and gay student groups and positive discussions of gay
issues from university campuses.<P>

<a href="n012996.html">1/29 --  ACLU Urges Clinton to Veto Defense Bill Barring Abortions and HIV-Positive Troops</a>  The American Civil Liberties Union today called on
President Clinton to stand by his principles and veto a defense budget
bill that would deny abortions to military personnel and require the
Pentagon to discharge HIV-positive servicemembers.
<P>

<a href="n012396.html">1/23 --   ACLU Secures Final Victory in Groundbreaking AIDS Bias Case</a>  A $350,000 settlement was announced today in a lawsuit brought by the American Civil Liberties Union against a doctor and
hospital for refusing to treat a man with AIDS. 
<P>

<a href="n012296b.html">1/22 --  Death Row Prisoner To Face Firing Squad In Utah;  ACLU, Rights Groups Mobilize Opposition</a>  The American Civil Liberties Union and Amnesty
International are mobilizing human rights, civil liberties and abolitionist
groups to mount a strong protest to the firing squad execution of John Albert
Taylor.
<P>

<a href="n012296c.html">1/22 --  High Court Denies Gov. Wilson's Petition to Stop Motor Voter</a><br>
This morning, the U.S. Supreme Court refused to reconsider a decision by
the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeal requiring California to implement the
National Voter Registration Act (NVRA), popularly called the motor voter law.
<p>

<a href="n012296.html">1/22 --  ACLU Marks Roe v. Wade Anniversary With Call to Action; Mobilizes Opposition to Late-Term Abortion Ban</a>  The American Civil Liberties Union today marked the 23rd anniversary of
Roe v. Wade.
<P>
<a href="n011696b.html">1/16 --  U.S. Supreme Court Reviews VMI's All-Male Policy;  ACLU Urges Justices to Adopt  Strict Scrutiny' Approach to Sex Discrimination</a>  The United States Supreme Court will hear argument tomorrow in
a challenge to the Virginia Military Institute's policy of excluding all
women.
<P>
<a href="n011696.html">1/16 --  Test Case Challenge to the Military's Ban on Gays Argued Before Federal Appeals Court in New York</a>  A constitutional challenge to the Clinton Administration's ban on gays
in the military was argued today before a  federal appeals court in New York. 
<p>
<a href="n011296.html">1/12 -- ACLU and Native Americans in Montana File Lawsuit Under Voting Rights Act</a>  The American Civil Liberties Union and the Indian Law Center today filed a major federal lawsuit challenging Montana's legislative districts for diluting the voting power of the state's large Native American population.
<P><a href="n011096.html">1/10 -- Discrimination Complaint Filed Against Pitt Over Refusal To Give Health Benefits To Same Sex Partners</a>  The American Civil Liberties Union announced today that a
complaint has been filed with the Pittsburgh Human Relations Commission against the
University of Pittsburgh.
<P><a href="n010596.html">1/5 -- Wyoming Supreme Court Upholds Visitation Restrictions on Lesbian Mother </a>  The highest court in Wyoming upheld restrictions on the right of a lesbian mother to visit her two children.
<p>
<a href="n010396.html">1/3 -- CA Supreme Court To Hear Key Abortion Rights Case Medical Groups Oppose Restricting Teenagers' Access To Abortion</a>  On January 10, the California Supreme Court will hear oral arguments in the case challenging the 1987 California law requiring minors to obtain parental or judicial consent for abortions. <P>

 
</a>
<p>

