<blockquote>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/newshdr.gif"><P>
<center>
<h1> ACLU Press Releases</h1>
</center>
<P>
<h3>November 1995</h3>

<a href="n112295.html">11/22 -- Federal Judge Rules California May Not Enforce Immigration and Throws Out Major Portions of Prop. 187 As Unconstitutional</a><P>
<a href="n1116953.html">11/16 -- ACLU Foundation of Utah Files Federal Discrimination Suit Against Ogden-Based Solaray, Inc
</a>
<br>In a summary judgement ruling issued Nov. 20 confirming exclusive federal authority over immigration, U.S.
     District Court Judge Mariana Pfaelzer said major portions of Prop. 187 are unconstitutional, thus eliminating the
     need for a trial on those specific provisions. 
<P>
<a href="n111695-.html">11/16 -- ACLU Foundation of Utah Files Federal Discrimination Suit Against Ogdeon-Based Solaray, Inc. 
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union Foundation of Utah today
     filed suit in U.S. District Court against Ogden-based Solaray, Inc., charging the company violated the Americans
     with Disabilites Act (ADA) when it fired an employee infected with the Human Immunodeficency Virus. 
<p>
<a href="n1116952.html">11/16 -- Oregon ACLU Will Not Represent Anti-Abortion Activists in Planned Parenthood Lawsuit
</a>
<br>The ACLU of Oregon announced Thursday it has decided it will not defend any of the anti-abortion activists
     named in the $200 million class action lawsuit filed last month by Planned Parenthood. 
<P>
<a href="n1116951.html">11/16 -- Workers At Hillhaven Charge Convalescent Home With Language Discrimination
</a>
<br>Nine current and former workers at a San Rafael nursing home owned by the Hillhaven Corporation, the largest
     nursing home chain in the United States, are accusing their employer of violating federal and state civil rights laws
     by implementing a "speak-English-only" policy.
<P>
<a href="n111695.html">11/16 -- ACLU Urges Senate Judiciary Committee to Oppose Ban on Certain Abortions
</a>
<br>
<P>
<a href="n111395.html">11/13 -- ACLU Annual Bill of Rights Day Celebration
</a>
<br>The ACLU of Northern California will hold its annual Bill of Rights Day Celebration on Sunday, December 3 at
     the Sheraton Palace Hotel in San Francisco with keynote speaker Linda Ellerbee and honoree Ernest Besig,
     founder of the ACLU-NC. 
<P>
<a href="n1109954.html">11/9 -- Claims of Abraham Ahmad and Family Under the Federal Tort Claims Act
</a>
<br>This letter serves as a joint claim for damages under the Federal Tort Claims Act filed on behalf of Abraham
     Ahmad, his wife Martina Ahmad, and their minor children, Sanna and Nesreen Ahmad.
<P>
<a href="n1109953.html">11/9 -- Statement of Louis M. Bograd Counsel, ACLU National Legal Department
</a>
<br>The bombing of the Alfred P. Murrah federal building in Oklahoma City on April 19th of this year was a terrible
     tragedy. That tragedy was compounded by the United States government's investigation of the bombing, when
     various government employees detained and mistreated Abraham Ahmad without cause, solely because of his
     ethnicity.
<P>
<a href="n1109952.html">11/9 -- Statement of Abraham Ahmad at News Conference Announcing Filing of Claim Against U.S. Government
</a>
<br>My name is Abraham Ahmad, and I am an ordinary American citizen. I am filing this claim today with the ACLU
     because ethnic stereotype should never again be the sole basis for a criminal investigation. No one should ever
     have to go through the mistreatment I faced during those three days, and what my family has faced since. 
<P>
<a href="n1109951.html">11/9 -- ACLU Files Claim Against U.S. Government on Behalf of Jordanian-American Wrongly Detained for Oklahoma City Bombing
</a>
<br> The American Civil Liberties Union today announced the filing of a claim on behalf of
     Abraham Ahmad, a Jordanian-American who was wrongly detained in connection with the Oklahoma City
     bombing. 
<P>
<a href="n110995.html">11/9 -- ACLU Challenges Federal Employee Gag Law
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union of the National Capital Area filed suit in federal court
     here today challenging the constitutionality of a law that prohibits federal workers from speaking on behalf of
     organizations in proceedings before federal agencies involving policy matters. 
<P>
<a href="n110895.html">11/8 -- ACLU Commends Senate Vote on Abortion Procedure; Urges Senators to Ultimately Defeat Ban
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union commended the Senate today for sending back to
     committee the so-called "Partial Birth Abortion Ban Act." 
<P>
<a href="n110795.html">11/7 -- ACLU Asks U.S. Supreme Court to Extend Free Speech Protection to Vietnam Vetern Who Reveres the American Flag
</a>
<br> The American Civil Liberties Union has asked the U.S. Supreme Court to rule that a retired
     Army Major and Vietnam veteran who refuses to wear a mandatory American flag patch on his State corrections
     officer uniform, for reasons of patriotism and reverence for the flag, is entitled to constitutional protection. 
<P>
<a href="n1102952.html">11/2 -- ACLU Says That FBI Proposal On Wiretapping Would Make the KGB Look Like Privacy Advocates
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union today emphatically urged the FBI to withdraw its
     proposal for greatly increased wiretapping powers. 
<P>
<a href="n110295.html">11/2 -- ACLU to file Suit Challenging D.C. Curfew Law
</a>
<br>On Thursday, November 2, 1995, the American Civil Liberties Union of the National Capital Area will file a
     class-action lawsuit against the District of Columbia challenging the D.C. juvenile curfew law on the grounds that it
     violates the First, Fourth, and Fifth Amendments to the United States Constitution. 
<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A><P>
