<IMG SRC="/graphics/newshdr.gif"><P>
<center>
<h1> ACLU Press Releases</h1>
</center>
<P>
<h3>May 1995</h3>

<a href="n052595.html">5/25 -- ACLU Buckhannon
</a>
<br>The West Virginia Civil Liberties Union goes to court on Tuesday, May 30, in
     Clarksburg to argue that schools should not be used as a site for local merchants to distribute bibles. 

<P>
<a href="n052495.html">5/24 -- Is It Over? ACLU Report Says Decades of Voting Rights Progress Endangered; Supreme Court Will Determine Fate in Pending Decisions
</a>
<br> Rebutting what it calls misguided and often racist criticism, the American Civil Liberties Union
     today issued a major report warning that perhaps the most effective civil rights law ever enacted -- the Voting
     Rights Act of 1965 -- is in danger of being gutted by the Supreme Court this term. 

<P>
<a href="n052495a.html">5/24 -- Media Advisory; Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals to Hear Turic V. Holland Hospitality; Employment Discrimination for Considering Abortion
</a>
<br>Was Kimberly Turic fired for contemplating having an abortion? If so, did that action violate the Pregnancy
     Discrimination Act? 

<P>
<a href="n052395.html">5/23 -- ACLU Opens Constitution Hall on America Online; AOL, ACLU Join in Partnership Dedicated to the Principle of Free Speech
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union, the nation's oldest and largest civil liberties organization,
     said today that it has joined with America Online in launching a new educational interactive forum dedicated to the
     principle of free speech. 

<P>
<a href="n051795.html">5/17 -- Language of Christian Coalition Contract Obscures Radical Ideas; ACLU Calls on Congress to Reject Attacks on Traditional American Values
</a>
<br> The American Civil Liberties Union today called on Congress to reject the radical ideas
     embedded in the Christian Coalition's newly proposed Contract with the American Family. 

<P>
<a href="n051595a.html">5/16 -- First International Survey of Prayer in Schools Finds That World's Major Countries Reject State-Sanctioned School Prayer
</a>
<br>A school prayer amendment to the U.S. Constitution being pushed by conservative groups
     and Republicans would put the United States squarely at odds with most of the world's nations, according to an
     international survey issued today by the ACLU of Southern California. 

<P>
<a href="n051595b.html">5/15 -- ACLU Launches Preemptive Strike on Christian Coalition
</a>
<br>Letter to President, Congress, All Governors Warning of Proposed Contract with the American Family' 

<P>
<a href="n051595.html">5/15 -- ACLU Launches; Letter to President Clinton
</a>
<br>This week, the Christian Coalition is expected to unveil a set of legislative proposals marketed as a "Contract with
     the American Family." Its centerpiece is reported to be a proposed constitutional amendment to protect "religious
     expression" in the public schools. 

<P>
<a href="n051295.html">5/12 -- Sixth Circuit Reverses Issue 3 Decision ACLU Announces Appeal in Cincinnati Anti-Gay Initiative Case
</a>
<br>

<P>
<a href="n051195.html">5/11 -- Statement of Janet Gallagher, Director, ACLU's National Reproductive Freedon and Women's Rights Projects on Violence Against Women's Health Clinics
</a>
<br>"The American Civil Liberties Union today applauds the Senate Committee on Appropriations, Subcommittee on
     Labor, HHS, and Education for addressing the epidemic of violence against reproductive health clinics and
     women seeking their services. 

<P>
<a href="n050495.html">5/4 -- Federal Judge Invalidates City of Cleveland's Tax on Sidewalk Newspaper Distributors
</a>
<br>A Federal judge yesterday invalidated a Cleveland peddler's ordinance which required
     homeless persons and members of the Nation of Islam to buy a $50 permit before distributing their respective
     newspapers on city sidewalks. 

<P>
<a href="n050295e.html">5/2 -- ACLU Background Briefing: The Unmasked Threat of Counterterrorism Legislation
</a>
<br>Last month, the ACLU distributed a background briefing on an important, if not very high
     profile, proposal by the Clinton Administration that we feared would slip through Congress without much public
     attention.

<P>
<a href="n050295f.html">5/2 -- ACLU Background Briefing: Big Brother Is Alive and Getting Bigger
</a>
<br> Big Brother is alive and well and growing even bigger in the nation's capital. Americans
     today face the most serious threats to their personal privacy rights since the Watergate years. The image of an
     intrusive Big Brother government that can watch every individual and can know the details of each individual's
     personal life is not a paranoid delusion.

<P>
<a href="n050295d.html">5/2 -- ACLU Background Briefing: Crime Bills Tread Heavily On Fundamental Liberties
</a>
<br>With crime still high on the public's list of what is wrong with America, Congress can be
     expected to steamroll toward passage of a harsh, but ineffective, omnibus crime bill in the next 100 days. As in
     past years, current proposals tread heavily on fundamental civil liberties without increasing public safety.

<P>
<a href="n050295c.html">5/2 -- ACLU Background Briefing: The first Amendment.  The First To Go?
</a>
<br>The First Amendment to the United States Constitution is often characterized as a first
     among equals. Its protections guaranteeing free speech, free press and free association -- and its twin guarantees
     of religious liberty -- are the cornerstones of our American society. 

<P>
<a href="n050295b.html">5/2 -- ACLU Background Briefing: Congress Launches Hidden Assault on Civil Liberties</a>
<P>
<a href="n050295.html">5/2 -- ACLU Background Briefing: Congress Launches Hidden Assault on Civil Liberties
</a>
<br>The symbolic first 100 days of the 104th Congress may be over, but the grave dangers
     posed to civil liberties are just now becoming clear.

<P>
<a href="n050295a.html">5/2 -- ACLU Launches New Communications Efforts: America Online Forum Opens Tomorrow, Daily & Quarterly Bulletins To Start Soon
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union today said that it is launching three new major
     communications strategies in an effort to unmask the hidden assault on civil liberties that is now underway in
     Washington. 



