<center>
<h1> ACLU Press Releases</h1>
</center>
<P><h3>April 1995</h3>

<a href="n042795.html">4/27 -- Senate Bars Bill of Rights at Terrorism Hearings; ACLU Decries Decision Not To Allow Civil Liberties Groups to Testify
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union today stood outside the Senate office building, literally
     barred from testifying before the Senate Judiciary Committee about the civil liberties concerns regarding proposed
     anti-terrorism legislation, and urged Congress and the Administration to move methodically in considering its
     response to the tragedy of the Oklahoma City bombing. 

<P>
<a href="n042695.html">4/26 -- Open Letter to President Clinton and Congressional Leadership A Joint Letter From a Coalition of Diverse Organizations Concerned About Civil Rights
</a>
<br>In the current climate of understandable fury at the bombing in Oklahoma City and of
     justifiable pride in the accomplishments of the FBI and other law enforcement organizations, we urge you to
     examine any new counterterrorism proposals with calm deliberation and in light of their constitutional implications.

<P>
<a href="n042495.html">4/24 -- ACLU Denounces Clinton Administration Proposals on Terrorism; Urges Government Not To Sacrifice Individual Liberty and Freedom
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union today said that the "counter-terrorism" proposals suggested
     by President Clinton Sunday evening threatened to repeat the mistakes of the past and erode constitutional
     principles that have shaped our society and remain at the core of our freedom and liberty. 

<P>
<a href="n042195b.html">4/21 -- ACLU Urges Police Commission to Exercise Caution in Developing Wholesale Revisions to Police Terrorist Investigation Guidelines
</a>
<br> The ACLU of Southern California on Friday cautioned the Los Angeles Police Commission
     not to abandon standards that guard against unwarranted police surveillance in the commission's accelerated
     review of revisions to guidelines for investigations of alleged terrorist groups. 

<P>
<a href="n042195a.html">4/21 -- New Medicaid Abortion Regulations Challenged As Unconstitutional
</a>
<br> A coalition of physicians and organizations today filed suit on behalf of their patients and
     members seeking to continue coverage of medically necessary abortions for Medicaid-eligible New Mexican
     women. 

<P>
<a href="n042195.html">4/21 -- VA Supreme Court Denies Custody to Sharon Bottoms; ACLU Vows To Continue Legal Challenges
</a>
<br>The Virginia Supreme Court today denied Sharon Bottoms, a lesbian mother, custody of her son, Tyler. The
     American Civil Liberties Union, which represents Ms. Bottoms, denounced the decision and vowed to continue
     its two-year battle to reunite mother and child.

<P>
<a href="n041995.html">4/19 -- Janet Gallagher Named to Top ACLU Post; ACLU Continues Fight For Women's Rights, Reproductive Freedom
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union has appointed Janet Gallagher, a long-time women's
     movement activist and attorney, as Director of the ACLU's national Women's Rights and Reproductive Freedom
     Projects. 

<P>
<a href="n041995a.html">4/19 -- ACLU of Texas Files Lawsuit Defending Religious Freedom for Prisoners
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union of Texas announced today that it was filing a lawsuit on behalf of
     13 prisoners whose religious freedom have been violated by the Texas Department of Criminal Justice. 

<P>
<a href="n041795.html">4/17 -- ACLU Files In Groudbreaking Computer Obscenity Case
</a>
<br>ACLU Files In Groundbreaking Computer Obscenity Case; Friend-of-the-Court Brief Seeks to Overturn
     Tennessee Conviction 

<P>
<a href="n041395.html">4/13 -- ACLU Endorses Joint Statement on Religion & Public Schools
</a>
<br> The American Civil Liberties Union is pleased to be here today to join with a wide
     array of other religious and secular organizations in releasing this important and timely joint statement of current
     law regarding religion in our public schools. 


<P>
<a href="n041295.html">4/12 -- Administration's Proposed Secrecy Rules Violate Privacy Rights; ACLU Vows To Challenge Proposal
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union today criticized the Clinton administration for
     proposing rules governing access to classified information that would trample the privacy rights of the two million
     Americans who hold security clearances, as well as those who would seek the clearances in the future. 

<P>
<a href="n041195b.html">4/11 -- Two Gay Men Vindicated in ACLU CASE; Jury Awards $11,000 for Brutality By 3 DEA Agents
</a>
<br>Two gay men who were beaten and unlawfully arrested by three federal Drug Enforcement
     agents in 1988 were vindicated today by a jury in Manhattan, who found that the defendants violated the civil
     rights of the two plaintiffs, Marc J. Anderson and Jeffrey E. Grubb.

<P>
<a href="n041195a.html">4/11 -- A Brave First Step: ACLU Commends U.S. Sentencing Commission For Equitable Decision; Says Congress Must Now End Disparity Between Crack, Powder Cocaine
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union today commended the U.S. Sentencing
     Commission for taking a brave first step toward ending the disparity in sentencing between crack and powder
     cocaine. 

<P>
<a href="n041195.html">4/11 -- ACLU Urges Judge Ito To Unseal Transcripts of Jury Dismissal Hearings Held in Chamber in O.J Simpson Double Murder Trial
</a>
<br>The ACLU Foundation of Southern California on Tuesday urged Superior Court Judge
     Lance Ito to release transcripts of in-chambers hearings at which jurors have been dismissed in the O.J. Simpson
     murder trial. 

<P>
<a href="n040495.html">4/4 -- ACLU of Texas Files A Complaint Against Santa Fe ISD
</a>
<br>The ACLU of Texas, acting on behalf of parents and students in Santa Fe, today filed a complaint
     against Santa Fe ISD for numerous violations of the First Amendment's prohibition against government
     establishment of religion. 
