<P>
<h3>January 1995</h3>

<a href="n013195.html">1/31 -- ACLU of Maryland Charges Decades of Baltimore Housing Discrimination
</a>
<br> The American Civil Liberties Union of Maryland today announced filing of a lawsuit on behalf
     of all African American families living in Baltimore City's public housing who for decades have been denied
     housing choice based on their race. 

<P>
<a href="n012595.html">1/25 -- LAPD Settles ACLU Sexual Assault Case for $165,000; Case Symbolizes Persistent Sexual Harassment, Gender Inequities
</a>
<br>As jurors were about to return a verdict, the City of Los Angeles and Los Angeles Police
     Department officials agreed to pay $165,000 to a former female officer raped by a male colleague on Police
     Academy grounds in 1990 in a case that symbolizes persistent sexual harassment and gender equity shortcomings
     in the LAPD.
<P>
<a href="n012495.html">1/24 -- ACLU Foundation of Southern California Center for Constitutional Rights National Lawyers Guild
</a>
<br>Federal Judge Rules Government Cannot Use Secret Evidence In Long-Running Deportation Case Against Palestinians
<P>
<a href="n012395.html">1/23 -- ACLU, Others Welcome Federal Lawsuit on Motor Voter Law
</a>
<br> The U.S. Department of Justice announced today that it is filing a federal lawsuit to force
     California to obey the 1993 National Voter Registration Act, a move hailed today by the ACLU of Southern
     California, the Lawyer's Committee for Civil Rights of the San Francisco Bay Area and others involved in the
     struggle to close the gap between minority and white voting registration rates. 

<P>
<a href="n012095a.html">1/20 -- Federal Appeals Court to Hear Challenge to NJ Ban on Graduation Prayer
</a>
<br>The Black Horse Pike School District's appeal of an injunction against any form of prayer at its graduation
     ceremonies, secured by the American Civil Liberties Union of New Jersey on behalf of a 1993 graduating
     student, will be heard on Monday, January 23, by the federal Third Circuit Court of Appeals in Philadelphia. 
<P>
<a href="n012095.html">1/20 -- Student Strip Searches: Lawsuit Filed Against Seattle School District; Settlements Announced in Two Other Washington Cities
</a>
<br>The American Civil Liberties Union of Washington announced the filing of a lawsuit today against
     the Seattle School District on behalf of a male elementary school student who was strip-searched in 1993 by his
     female teacher. 
<P>
<a href="n011895.html">1/18 -- Judge Signs Order Blocking Prop 187; State Officials Enjoined From Enforcing Anti-Immigrant Measure
</a>
<br>U.S. District Court Judge Mariana Pfaelzer signed a written order late today outlining the conditions of the
     preliminary injunction she granted Dec. 14 blocking implementation of the education, health, social services and
     reporting provisions of Prop. 187. 
<P>
<a href="n011795.html">1/17 -- Judge Bars The Office of the Attorney General From Secretly Subpoenaing the Confidential Medical and Financial Records of California Citizens
</a>
