<TITLE>ACLU in Congress: Roe v. Wade Anniversary</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><IMG SRC="/graphics/repro.gif"></P>
<P><B><FONT SIZE="+2">On</FONT> the 24th Anniversary</B> of the Supreme Court
ruling in <I>Roe v. Wade</I> legalizing abortion, the ACLU:</P>
<UL>
<LI> announces a <A HREF="/news/n012297a.html">new director of its
Reproductive Freedom Project,</A> </LI>
<LI>invites you to learn more about the <A HREF="/issues/reproduct/about.html">ACLU's
Reproductive Freedom Project</A></LI>
<LI>and urges you read on about threats to safe and legal abortion in the
upcoming session of Congress and state legislatures, and learn what you can do
to help protect the health and safety of women.</LI></UL>
<HR>
<H2 ALIGN="CENTER">STOP CONGRESS FROM CRIMINALIZING SAFE ABORTION PROCEDURES!</H2>
<P>Congress is once again gearing up to enter the operating room and pass
legislation to criminalize a rarely used  abortion procedure, misleadingly
refered to by anti-choice extremists as &quot;partial birth abortions.&quot; 
</P>
<P>Known by physicians as &quot;dilation and extraction,&quot; the procedure is
often performed in cases where the pregnancy has gone tragically wrong. Of the
available techniques, it is among the safest and offers women the best chance of
preserving their future fertility. </P>
<P>But the technique has been distorted and sensationalized by the anti-choice
movement. Last year, the Senate was short a mere 9 votes to override President
Clinton's veto of a bill that would have outlawed the procedure, representing
the first time ever that the federal government attempted to ban a particular
medical procedure.   </P>
<P>Anti-choice forces inside and outside of Congress are now building momentum
for passing a measure in the 105th Congress.  It must be countered by an even
stronger outpouring of pro-choice voices.</P>
<P>Help us to protect the health and safety of women and urge state and federal
decisionmakers not to deny women the right to a necessary medical procedure.</P>
<UL>
<LI>Send our model <A HREF="/issues/reproduct/latetermlet.html">letter</A> to
your state or federal representatives.  Use our <A HREF="/action/concong.html">congressional
lookup</A> to fax or e-mail members of congress.</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/action/mailist.html">Sign up</A> to receive congressional action
alerts as specific late term bills see are introduced. (Select the &quot;action&quot;
mailing list.)</LI>
<LI>Bookmark this page for further updates at your own convenience.</LI></UL>
